HEADWORD: Malaxis-unifolia
<hw>Malaxis-unifolia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A North American orchid
having a solitary leaf and flowers with threadlike petals.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> green adder's mouth, <spn>Malaxis
ophioglossoides</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
